Name: disease of metabolism
Definition: A disease that involving errors in metabolic processes of building or degradation of molecules.

Name: disease by infectious agent
Definition: A disease that is the consequence of the presence of pathogenic microbial agents

Name: physical disorder
Definition: A disease that has_material_basis_in a genetic abnormality

Name: disease of cellular proliferation
Definition: A disease that is characterized by abnormally rapid cell division.

Name: disease of mental health
Definition: A disease that involves a psychological or behavioral pattern generally associated with subjective distress or disability that occurs in an individual

Name: syndrome
Definition: A disease characterized by a group of signs and symptoms that occur together and characterize a particular abnormality.
Synonym: Thoracic or lumbar spondylosis with myelopathy

Name: genetic disease
Definition: A disease that has_material_basis_in genetic variations in the human genome.

Name: obsolete prostate basal cell carcinoma
Definition: A disease that has_material_basis_in genetic variations in the human genome.
Synonym: basal cell carcinoma of the prostate

Name: disease of anatomical entity
Definition: A disease that manifests in a defined anatomical structure.
Synonym: recurrent squamous cell carcinoma of the lung

Name: obsolete lymphoid tissue disease
Definition: A disease that manifests in a defined anatomical structure.
Synonym: recurrent squamous cell carcinoma of the lung
